post_text:
Have you filled out your 2020 Census yet? 10 minutes will help ensure our community receives enough resources for 10 years. The Census provides funding for schools, hospitals, after-school programs and more! To fill out the census please visit my2020census.gov or call 844-330-2020 A special thanks to Grasiela Rodriguez for creating this amazing mural at Potrero School!
#CaStudentsCount #LACcensuschalkathon #WeCountLA

post_text:
Estimados padres, estudiantes y personal del distrito escolar de el distrito escolar de El Monte:

¡Estamos muy emocionados de darle la bienvenida al año escolar 2020-21! El primer día de clases es el 20 de agosto. A pesar de que estamos comenzando en el aprendizaje a distancia, ¡estamos ansiosos por "verlos"!

Este año, para celebrar el primer día de clases, les animamos a que publiquen una foto del primer día de clases y utilicen nuestro hashtag #EMCSDFirstDay en las redes sociales. ¡Lo invitamos a ayudarnos a compartir la alegría por el comienzo de nuestro nuevo año escolar!

Puede publicar fotos directamente en nuestras cuentas de EMCSD: Facebook @ElMonteCSD e Instagram @ElMonteCitysd . Dado que no podemos acceder a las fotos que publica en sus páginas personales de Facebook o Instagram, asegúrese de compartirlas con nosotros. También puede enviar sus fotos por correo electrónico a pics@emcsd.org , y con gusto las agregaremos a nuestro álbum de Regreso a la escuela.

¡Asegúrese de compartir sus recuerdos capturados con nosotros!

post_text:
Dear El Monte City School District, Parents, Students, and Staff,

We are very excited to welcome you to the 2020-21 school year! The first day of school is August 20th. Even though we are starting in distance learning, we can't wait to "see" you!

This year, to celebrate the first day of school, we are encouraging you to post first day of school pictures and use our hashtag #EMCSDFirstDay on social media. We invite you to help us spread cheer for the start of our new school year!

You can post photos directly to our EMCSD accounts: Facebook @ElMonteCSD and Instagram @ElMonteCitySD. Since we are unable to access photos you post on your personal Facebook or Instagram pages, make sure you share them with us. You can also email your photos to pics@emcsd.org, and we will happily add them to our Back to School album.

Be sure to share your captured memories with us!

post_text:
Cleminson School, one of five 2020 California Distinguished Schools in the El Monte City School District, has just completed a remarkable four years, being recognized as a California Distinguished School in both 2018 and 2020. Principal Carlos Salcedo believes that its success is due to Cleminson’s focusing on building relationships within the school community and its focus on data and improving the educational attainment of all students.

post_text: Check out our Shirpser School Staff Spotlight!
shared_text:
Shirpser
June 24 at 2:20 PM ·

Meet Ms. Dominguez, 5th grade teacher. She is about to begin her 35th year of teaching in the district. She is an alumni from Cal State LA and loves reading & playing card games. But her ultimate favorite past time is playing with her 3 grandchildren, soon to be 4. Ms. Dominguez wants all students to know, "don't be afraid to make mistakes."

Conozca a la Sra. Domínguez, maestra de 5to grado. Está a punto de comenzar sus 35 años de enseñanza en el distrito. Ella es una ex alumna de Cal State LA y le encanta leer y jugar juegos de cartas. Pero su pasatiempo favorito es jugar con sus 3 nietos, que pronto serán 4. La Sra. Domínguez quiere que todos los estudiantes sepan, "no tengan miedo de cometer errores".

Las lecciones están categorizadas por Artes del Lenguaje Inglés y Matemáticas, los estudiantes deben trabajar en una o dos lecciones por día por cada área temática. Se ha proporcionado una lista de actividades para la práctica de habilidades en Artes del Lenguaje Inglés y Matemáticas que no requieren hojas de trabajo o plan curricular. Además, para nuestros estudiantes del (Kinder Transicional) TK al 8 (octavo) grado que tienen acceso a Internet y computadoras, computadoras portátiles, Chromebooks o iPads pueden tener acceso a instrucción en línea por medio de i-Ready y ST Math, iniciando sesión en Clever usando su correo electrónico de distrito.
https://bit.ly/2xNEsBl

Our district has created a list of optional activities and resources, as well as enrichment in English Language Arts and Math to support students during school closures.

Additionally, for our K-8 students who have Internet access and computers, laptops, Chromebooks or iPads, i-Ready online instruction and ST Math are accessible by signing onto Clever using their district email (directions for accessing your student’s Clever account are included in the grade level links below).

If you have any questions regarding the lessons that have been provided, please contact your school administrator.
